Velocity component X (AU day⁻¹) – optional
float


vy
Velocity component Y (AU day⁻¹) – optional
float


vz
Velocity component Z (AU day⁻¹) – optional
float


roll
Roll angle (deg) – optional
float


pitch
Pitch angle (deg) – optional
float


yaw
Yaw angle (deg) – optional
float


name
Human‑readable identifier (e.g. Voyager‑1) – optional, otherwise the file basename is used
string


color_r,g,b
Display colour (0‑255) – optional; default = (255,255,255)
int


If velocity columns are missing the script will compute them by finite‑difference on the supplied positions.  Attitude columns are optional – they are stored in the JSON but are not used by the visualiser unless you map them to a rotation gizmo.
A JSON file may be used instead; it must be a list of objects with the same keys (time_iso, x, y, …).

